Human Rights Watch highlighted Beijing's efforts to develop China's western regions, leading to forced resettlements in Tibet and neighboring areas.
Tibetan herders were required to sell their livestock and move to new townships, disrupting their traditional way of life.
Farmers in Gansu province are being displaced to combat desertification, sparking resistance.
Despite government initiatives to reverse soil erosion and enhance water storage, challenges persist.
The State Forestry Administration is working to prevent further erosion through afforestation and pasture management.
Soil conservation efforts have boosted grain production and improved livelihoods for millions affected by erosion.
China aims to address soil erosion and protect arable land through sustainable agricultural practices
